1
00:00:00,334 --> 00:00:02,167
This was the choir place

2
00:00:02,209 --> 00:00:03,876
Girls used to come here and sing

3
00:00:04,209 --> 00:00:06,626
And perform church hymns

4
00:00:07,209 --> 00:00:08,209
There was an organ here

5
00:00:09,417 --> 00:00:13,209
It was played by Janet, the priest’s daughter, here

6
00:00:14,584 --> 00:00:16,042
The choir girls, all here

7
00:00:16,250 --> 00:00:17,959
They were many, about 20

8
00:00:18,250 --> 00:00:19,250
Over time

9
00:00:20,709 --> 00:00:24,209
In the 1990s, the number grew to around 60 people

10
00:00:25,167 --> 00:00:27,709
People emigrated and left because of the miserable conditions

11
00:00:28,667 --> 00:00:30,250
In the end only 10 people remained

12
00:00:31,125 --> 00:00:32,834
ISIS came and no one was left

13
00:00:33,709 --> 00:00:35,334
This was their place

14
00:00:37,125 --> 00:00:40,250
Interviewer: This choir you told us about

15
00:00:40,334 --> 00:00:43,584
At what time did you practice it exactly, and in which rites?

16
00:00:43,584 --> 00:00:44,876
Witness: During Mass, on Friday

17
00:00:45,834 --> 00:00:47,417
We deacons would sing from below

18
00:00:47,751 --> 00:00:49,125
Like question and answer

19
00:00:49,167 --> 00:00:50,250
And they would chant from here

20
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:53,125
We performed the hymns here on Friday

21
00:00:54,751 --> 00:00:56,551
And on all feast days, here
